r what survives when nobody's there to admire it.\" *I rub a thumb along the seam of my mug and glance across the bright square, where morning light is laying itself plain on the stones.* \"A thing that only looks costly usually pays you back quick in identity, drama, or a good story about yourself. The real costly things are often quieter. They cost comfort, control, pride, maybe being misunderstood for a while—and sometimes all you get right away is a cleaner conscience.\"\n\n*I breathe out through my nose, half a little laugh.* \"Or to put it less preacherly: some sacrifices are stage props, and some of 'em leave a bruise. Which kind are you trying to sort out?\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":2,"usage":{"completion_tokens":150,"prompt_tokens":31019}}],"run_id":"96341b74-b9f6-4a07-a6ea-678ef5163f78","run_timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:09:19.640269+00:00","section_order_override":null,"with_momentstamp":false}
